reviews.text:
Play has a really great vibe to it.  The ambience is really lovely, classy and relaxed.  It's a really beautiful space and well spaced out, so you have some privacy at your table. Service here is stellar and staff are particularly knowledgeable about the options and the wine list.   

There are many vegetarian and even vegan options!  I really appreciate this.  They even have a separate menu indicating the vegetarian and vegan options, to simplify your selection.  I really like the small plates served here, as I am often indecisive and can't choose what to order.  I believe I ordered two small plates and a drink, which was enough to satisfy me.  The food was really tasty and there are many different options to satisfy your palate.  

Prices were far more reasonable than I would have expected for a nicer spot, particularly a nicer spot that is in the market! 

I will definitely return here and I would most certainly recommend it.

Delicious food with creative use of ingredients and great staff. Lots of gluten free choices.

Really enjoyed the Crispy Tofu and Gnocchi. Their charcuterie board and cheese selections were very good as well. Didn't enjoy the beef tartar.

“Gastronomy & Ambiance at its Excellence!”

I went there with my partner last night and it turned out to be one of our best experiences at a fine cuisine. 
To give a laconic description, the atmosphere is romantic and pleasant, the staffs are very friendly and professional, and the small dishes taste amazing and definitely like nothing you have had before. 

Now a more detailed review: 
The very friendly waitress brought us water and explained the menu. The menu consists of many some basic cured meat (in their Charcuterie menu) and various mini courses (in their Savoury menu), as well cheese plates, sweets, and sides. The waitress recommended us to have three choices from the savoury menu. Also, each savoury comes with a paired wine. 
For our first round, we ordered Bean Salad and Albacore Tuna. The bean salad was one of the tastiest vegetable mixes I have had! The Albacore Tune was also very tasty and was served with Beet Sauce! Luscious! 
Before we could finish our first round of orders, the waitress came to us with a full blown trout dish, served to us for gratuity! Fantastic and Impressive! I believe every fine cuisine should do something to impress their customer and they absolutely did it! :) 
For our second round gnocchi and beef and it was again fantastic! By the time we finished our second dish + gratuity dish, we were full and happy!
We will definitely come back here, not to stuff ourselves, but to enjoy fantastic combinations that cannot be done at home!

Service was excellent! I was on my own so they sat me upstairs infront of the kitchen so i could see all the different dishes coming through. The chef every now and again would lean over and describe the different dishes - just a nice little touch. The waitress was really great. Food was tasty. Astmosphere was relaxed but felt vibrant. Just an excellent experience overall!

The small plates at play are always of high quality and the staff can perfectly pair every dish with a glass of wine. Play Food & Wine offers two floors of seating, so it is a good option if you have a larger group.

reviews.text:
The food is amazing; the service is just ok.

First, the good.  The food! This may well have been the best pasta I have ever eaten outside of Italy, and I have eaten in more than my fair share of restaurants.  The pasta was perfectly cooked, the sauce was creamy without being cloying or sweet, and it had just the right amount of acidity. The portions were adequate to satisfy a hungry diner and the presentation was lovely (I do appreciate the simplicity of a large, white pasta plate). This chef clearly knows what he is doing.

The food was priced right, running about $20 for an entree and $12 for an appetizer. A decent wine can be had for about $8/glass. 

I loved the atmosphere. The stone walls, lighting, and decor were very nice without being pretentious. It seems like it would be a good place for drinks  (there is a small bar) after a long  day working at the capitol, or to have a nice dinner. 

Now, the challenges they face. The service wasn't bad, but it could be improved. As i eat out often, and write prolifically about my dining experiences, I pay attention to the details. The weakest links in this restaurant are the hosts. The first time I went to VT, I left before being seated because the host seemed gleeful (yes, gleeful) to decline my accommodation request. I left so as to not let that negative experience taint my dining experience. The next night, I went again and the host  (different from the first night) was cavalier. It is unfortunate that the first person encountered by diners projects such negativity. However, if you are willing to be treated badly by the hosts, you are in for a great meal. 

Attire: You will probably feel most comfortable here wearing wearing business casual or business clothes as that is what most diners were wearing.

It started out disappointing. I made reservations and when I arrived it seemed they disappeared but we were lucky enough to be seated (Wasn't packed at the time). The menu has lots of variety and the cocktail menu as well.  The food when we got is was amazing! Overall good experience after the missing reservation situation.

This was my second time here for brunch. The first time was superb, and their version of eggs Benedict was done perfectly. This time, the eggs were cooked hard. When I mentioned it to the server, who is also the manager, she said that the cook makes them the way he likes, and that if I wanted them done a specific way I should have said something. Then she asked if I wanted the whole plate replaced or just the eggs. I said the latter, as not to be wasteful and because I was hungry and could snack on the sides. She came back with literally just the eggs. So i scooped up the little sauce I could to pour it on and place it on my now cold toast. When I later mentioned that usually the whole of the Benedict is usually replaced, as the toast is now cold and I have less sauce, she replied that I said I was okay with just the eggs and that I should have said that the toast was cold.I just figured that anyone who has eaten hot food, let alone is a manager of a restaurant, can deduce that food cools after 10 minutes. She kindly took 50% of the price of the dish, but did not do so for my dining partner, who had the same issues but was less vocal. I would never bother writing this long review if a simple mistake was made. I am doing so because lack of accountability, and blaming of the customer, is unacceptable.

We had the escargot, octopus salad, and tried two pasta dishes. Everything was delicious, properly cooked and well balanced in flavour. The house wine was good.

reviews.text:
My wife and I stopped in for lunch today. I had a Lone Star chicken salad which was really good. My wife had the Bruschetta and she also loved it.
The beers were nice and cold.
We were overall very pleased with the food and drinks.
However, the best part of our meal today was the 'service'
Our waitress 'Georgia260' was amazing. She was not only very pleasant to talk to, she was also caring, attentive and professional at the same time. 
5 stars for the food and 10 stars for the service.
We will definitely be going back for sure.
Good but gimmicky.  Service was good made it worth it. Overkill on the Texas theme and the waiter was named Maverick...God figure. Decent prices and choices.

This place is always packed. However, the service was great and the food was tasty. They do not take phone reservations but once we were assigned a table within a minute when we showed up. Prices are reasonable for what you get. I definitely recommend Lone Star.

Where: Lone Star Texas Grill, Ottawa
What: A tex Mex restaurant in downtown Ottawa
How was it: Good ambiance and good food.  They also have great chips and salsa - love it.  Fajitas are the way to go, but careful - you'll smell fajitas for some time !
Grade: Eli = 4, Serge = 4
Recommend: for sure !

I've been to other Lone Star's before and normally, it's fairly decent Tex-Mex, as far as Canadian standards go. However, at this location we visited as a large group, about 20-25 for our office Xmas lunch. Luckily for me, I did not order the fajitas because several of my co-workers did not show up to work today. Turns out they all ate the fajitas all fell ill with food poisoning. Suffice it to say, we will not be having our Xmas party lunch here again.

reviews.text:
The preamble: In fairness to restaurants we didn’t care for, we have omitted reviewing them. If your restaurant doesn't have a review on our board, we either didn’t love it, or we haven’t eaten there yet. If you are interested in having us dine at your establishment, send us a note and well get you on our list for future meals. We’re not here to trash the restaurants we believe have some work ahead of them, rather to applaud the restaurants we feel are above the bar.

Incredible brunch and lunch menus (sorry, no dinners). Go just after the lunch rush Monday to Friday, or show up early for the very busy weekend brunch. Interesting and sometimes changing menu including poached eggs, yukon potatoes and smoked salmon, or my favourite beautiful tuna loin with smoked tomato broth, chorizo balls and poached eggs. Great friendly service and interesting menu make this a must try place.
Ordered the sandwich. It was really great! The soup is also supreme!
Had a great breakfast here. Little touches on classic dishes made it so much more enjoyable. Great service, really inexpensive.
Good food and drinks.  Top notch customer services.

Nice place tucked behind the store front bakery. The service was friendly, and quite timely considering it was prime time for brunch on a Saturday. We had a 10 minute wait for a seat for two. The Kir Kir cocktail was great as was the hanger steak special. Expect to pay $15-20 each meal plus drinks which is reasonable for the quality of the food. Very flavorful.

One of my favourite spots to eat for lunch

My team and I go here pretty much everyday for lunch, especially for takeout. The prices are very reasonable and the quality high. They have weekly rotation of their salads and sandwiches or you can go custom. 

If you wish to sit down then the restaurant has really great pizzas, pastas, salads and drinks - definitely check it out.

Johnny Farina is a popular restaurant in downtown Ottawa, so it's good to make reservations before you arrive. The wine list and menu are extensive, and priced the way you'd expect for a downtown location. The staff is very accommodating, and paces the delivery of food and beverages the way you feel that evening. A Y was our server, and handled all requests with speed and a winning smile.
Delicious pizza & nice atmosphere. Gets very  busy at lunch, but staff gets the food out in a timely manner! Gets pretty loud at busy times, so maybe not the best date spot:)
Good food but service was slow. Bread should hit the table as soon as you order drinks and or took forever. Friendly enough though.
One of the nicest Italian places I have been too. Cozy restaurant with good flavours !

reviews.text: Was in this past saturday night for "Where's Mike" as it was their Grand Re-Opening from renovations this weekend. Truly an incredible experience! Amazing food, great staff, awesome band. Could not even recognize the place from the old bar before, it will not fail to please! Also i was very impressed with the quality of my steak, not a lot of places can get them right. Good job Greenfields!!!

We were in last Sunday night for dinner and had a great experience. I had the truffle burger and it was one of the best burgers I've ever had. The staff is wonderful and attentive as well. We will definitely be back and I would highly recommend checking this place out.

It was an ok place to have a pint. Not the original place. New atmosphere but service really was fake and more concerned about the size if your bill. Food was kinda rated just under McDonald's fare. Was looking for a nice place to sit and relax but was met with drivers who served you better service as your bill climbed. Not a place I would return to anytime soon. Owner was there and seemed to treat youlike a dollar sign instead of a true customer.

All I can say is fantastic. The Reno's are perfect for this type of bar.
Great job service and food.
New owners make this a completely new place. It is certainly one of the best spots in Barrhaven. Decent food and an OK beer selection. Nothing amazing but not bad either.

Great food and excellent service! Best Chinese in Ottawa.

formatted_address: Pinecrest Shopping Center, 2685 Iris St, Ottawa, ON K2C 3S4, Canada

reviews.text:
This is a restaurant review...  We all know IKEA so reviewing the store isn't necessary.  The restaurant used to be awesome.  Breakfast was affordable, a good value.  They have increased their prices so they could offer more choices and "free range eggs".  

The result is more fore less.  It's really not the deal it used to be.  I don't think we'll be coming back for breakfast.  It's a shame

Other food is alright, but it's budget food so it's really worth it when it's budget priced.  6.00 for the meatballs isn't worth it, but it's great when they go on sale.  The hotdogs/Ice cream are great, but they don't really hold a candle to Costco.

IKEA IS AN AWESOME PLACE TO GO FOR FURNITURE SHOPPING, BREAKFAST, SUPPER AND EVEN DINNER! THEIR PRICES ARE SO REASONABLE AND CHEAP! THEY ALSO HAVE AMAZING WORKERS THAT ARE SO POLITE AND PATIENT! THE WAY THEY ORGANIZED THERE STUFF IS INCREDIBLE AND SUPER NEAT! IF YOU ARE MOVING INTO A NEW HOME IKEA IS THE PERFECT PLACE TO GO TO FOR YOUR FURNITURE!

When shopping for furniture, Ikea is usually one of our first stops due to its great variety and selection as well as their nice showrooms which I give them points for. However when you take in account that nearly every piece of furniture need to be assemble greatly, that they charge a high fee for delivery to the point that it's cheaper to rent a van and that their prices are just a bit less than competitors with free shipping and furniture professionally assemble which lasts longer..... Ikea is really not an intelligent option, it is merely a lazy one, a one stop shop. If you look around at sales or are patient enough to wait for sales at other shops , you will find that they will be a better a option.

Do not leave your wife alone. If you do you will end up with a new living room set.

Since the renovations the layout has changed, with many more room displays to help you see how things could work together.

Great availability of the smaller items in the Market Hall....always dangerous for the impulse shopper.

The food is a GREAT value. Where else can you grab eggs and bacon for $1.00!!!!! Add to that the inexpensive hot-dog, drink, and/or frozen yogurt near the exit and you've got a quick meal that's cheaper than cooking for yourself.
My wife and I come here often to get ideas to decorate. They sell good everyday products at a great price. If you need something for your house this is the place to start.

Solid family restaurant with great breakfasts.

We arrived at noon and had a twenty minute wait.  Service was prompt after being seated with beverages arriving quickly.  The meals, though took over 1/2 hour.

Food good and facility a little scruffy but acceptable.  Manager admitted they were short staffed.

We returned for a second breakfast two days later.
Love the food and the portions are huge. Get there early or you'll have to wait for a table.

reviews.text: So happy to have chosen this spot for my birthday dinner! Fantastic food, I got the cod but most of the table went for the steak. I added the wine paring to my meal and would highly recommend doing so. Excellent service and great ambiance! We were a group of ten and were fit in perfectly at a long table. Can't wait to return soon.

A friend and I visited for a late dinner on  Friday night.   I ordered the BC Wild Cod steamed in coconut milk and served in a green curry sauce. It was very good, light and spicy.  Service was wonderful. The only drawback is that it was extremely noisy even though the restaurant was only one third occupied you could barely have a conversation with your dinner guest.

We went to absinthe for the fondue night. We chose the three course fondue, which was cheese, meat (oil), and chocolate. The food and drinks were excellent; it was the best fondue we have had in town. However, the service was terrible.
The front staff was very friendly, so it started out well. But in general, the servers were stiff, unfriendly, and ignored us for the majority of the meal. "Servers" because we had to wave down whichever staff was nearby multiple times to get any service at all. It was not a busy night, as fondue night is on Mondays, and there were three servers for 7 or 8 small tables. But we barely got a smile or a thank you from anyone, until we left. 
Really, the food was excellent, but we are hesitant to go back or recommend the restaurant to anyone, as the service left a foul taste in our mouths that overpowered the food. 
Food and drinks alone are 5 stars. But the service was 1. 
It really made me realise the importance of service and attitude.

Excellent dining experience. French inspired menu. Menu items supposedly prepared using seasonal & local ingredients. Great wine selection (and pairing suggestions). Good service. The decor is a bit bland but the food makes up for it.
I would easily recommend that anyone try this restaurant. The food is unique and how often do you get to try legit absinthe the way it was meant to be tried. It's an experience.

Whalesbone is well know for great oysters. Great place to go. Friendly staff and always good food
Some of the best food I've ever had, excellent service and a cozy atmosphere. Went there for an anniversary dinner and it was very romantic, just make sure you make a reservation.
Amazing food (oysters and more) and great staff. The clam chowder was delicious. We were able to walk in for lunch, but I would make reservations for dinner given the limited space.
Good food and beer selection

Standard Timmy's, no drive-through. No real parking; mostly foot traffic by the buses and between the Rideau Centre and the Market.

reviews.text: Worst Indian restaurant in Ottawa. No manners to the guy at cash counter/manager. Me and my friends reached at 1:20 to restaurant and the first thing we got was "be fast we are closing at 2". The thing i hated the most was the manager took plate from front of my friend who was on her phone and rudely told "eat food first because we are closing at 2" in between her call. He starts to stare at you from 1:30 as if he want you to just pay and leave. If you guys want to close why don't you lock the door at 1:30 so no new customer enter. First and last visit to this unwelcoming place. The one star is too just for the food that was average, except for the sweet dish specially GulabJamun which seemed like way too old.
Dinner is excellent, though not a lot of patrons in the evening. My mate liked it so much we went two nights in a row. Excellent price, and large quantities.
Best naan ever, so chewy and soft! Love their butter chicken. Does not disappoint!!

The tables are so densely packed that we could hold a conversation with the people sitting at the table next to ours, but the restaurant offers a buffet at a convenient location with a delicious selection at a reasonable price for a vegan.

The restaurant was clean.  The food was great.  The service was excellent.  Waiter was friendly with a sense of humour.  We will definately go back.  The only negative point was that the food had too much salt.

name: Black Tomato

reviews.text:
Happened upon this restaurant while on the way to another and after a quick review check decided to change our plans and go here instead. Went around the back to the beautiful courtyard and were lucky to be seated at one of the last remaining tables.

Speedy drink service and menu recommendations followed and the decisions were made. I had the baked brie which was perfect except I would leave out the "apple butter". It overpowered the other flavors. The chicken was next which was gorgeous! Exactly as described by the attentive waiter except for a surprise melted cheese on the vegetables. I felt it was out of place on the plate. 

We finished with the homemade peanut butter pie which we were told was baked fresh that day by the owners 84 year old mother! It was just super!! Would highly recommend a trip to The Black Tomato when in Ottawa.
Service was great. Servers obviously enjoying their jobs and interactions with customers. Food good as well. Server knew wine list and beer offerings well.

Amazing atmosphere, top notch cocktail list that is updated weekly, if not nightly. Great service, and even more personable staff. A great place to go for some drinks in the market, without all the noise and distractions that come with most other locales. A great place to bring a date for dinner and drinks, or just to unwind after a long day
Amazing green egg smoked burger! Priced fair and the staff was knowledgeable and friendly.
Server top notch. Atmosphere very unique and old world. Food done to perfection. Compared to the other courtyard restaurants the black tomato blows them out of the water.

adr_address: 44 Sparks St, Ottawa, ON K1P 5A8, Canada
formatted_address: 44 Sparks St, Ottawa, ON K1P 5A8, Canada
name: D'Arcy McGee's

reviews.text: This is one of my 'go to' places downtown. Always a great place to eat, drink and be merry with friends and family. Warm atmosphere. Friendly and helpful efficient staff. Good food and now the menu gives the caloric value of each item. Very helpful for diet conscious folks. I was pleased to find many vegetarian and gluten free options. Great beer selection on tap.

The Guinness Burger they serve here is one of the top 10 burgers I have ever had in my life (I eat burgers pretty well everywhere I go). It was so good that I ordered a second one while there, which is something I never do. Would highly recommend this burger to anyone else who really enjoys them. Will definitely be back for this burger next time I am in Ottawa.

The fries and chicken pie were good, but the burger was kinda small, though tasty. They serve goose island beer on special one day of the week. Overall, the food is generic.

Has a pub vibe and has sports stations showing. Lots of dark stain wood decor. Variety of seating with tables, high tops, bars, patio and banquets.

Service was okay. Bartender tried to overcharge for the beer that was on special.

Overall, I would not go back regularly.

This was my original revuew: "I like this pub a lot. Good food, good beers." but it feels like every time I go back, the menu changes and a favorite disappears. Sure I only go there 3-4 times a years, but that will go down to probably zero if the trend continues. Where are the crock, meatloaf and lava cake?

Took us in after the New Years fireworks on parliament hill. Despite the fact that they were being overrun by people looking for warmth and food they had good, pleasant sevice and a great live band -if a bit louder than necessary-

reviews.text: This place is right next to my work, and I often ask myself "Why don't I go here more often" and remember as I'm walking out feeling like crap. This place serves mediocre food at a premium price. The wait staff varies from OK to unattentive. They had a hot dog special where I ordered a 13$ hot dog. I thought "Wow this must be a pretty fancy hot dog!". Nope. I am not exaggerating when I say that a hot dog at Costco for 1.50$ tastes a LOT better, and that would have come with a soda. I will always attempt to talk my work out of ever returning for team meals, and hope that the 4-5 times I have been will never be repeated.
Good place for drinks but food could be better. Wings some time taste like fish.
Recently updated... but this has been a favorite of the Kanata tech area for years.    Cosy, not too loud,  food good, priced right,  service fast.
Very good service and pretty good food.  Not a bad spot to stop in for a snack and a beverage.
Royal Oak Kanata is an OK restaurant. The food is good, some unique items. The service can be slow at times.

adr_address: 281 Dalhousie St A, Ottawa, ON K1N 7E5, Canada
formatted_address: 281 Dalhousie St A, Ottawa, ON K1N 7E5, Canada
name: Subway

reviews.text: I've been to this location many times, it's my favourite location of all Subways, my colleagues do concur as well.  We work for the Goverment in the heart of the city. We have noticed the weekday, staff gives impeccable service. The washroom and place is always clean, fast and polite service. There's a redhead that works daytime shift If it wasn't for her we would not frequent this Subway! The lady owner is rude, complaining to her staff in front of customers!

Looks like the lady owner is ready for a corporate takeover; What a joke! I've seen this woman at another Subway before, she's unpleasant with customers, that mainly entails the yelling at her staff in front of customers, how unprofessional. I don't know which corperation she would take over, being that one of the first etiquettes of a boss is to treat your employees with respect. I would give a 5 star rating but I felt bad for the employees being treated like that. 
N.B  Fresh subs and clean place, most likely employees doing.

I couldnt understand what was going on. I would hate Subway if I havent tasted it before. Throw off most of it away, ingredients were not fresh.
Staff tried to be friendly, but could read their minds that even they were not pleased with the service they provided, exactly food. Though I read bad reviews  about this place  before going there, I thought it was just a case. So I proved  it is not only once. So, one should definitely take into consideration reviews.

I think this place is nice and good customer service my sub is always fresh. I've noticed out of all the Subway's downtown this is the cleanest one. I guarantee  you it's because of the red hair girl that always serves me. She has a great smile, great attitude and always engages me in conversation.

This subway is by far one of the best subways iv been to , the subs and cookies are always fresh and ready to go & there's very good customer service the young lady with the red hair is always polite and very welcoming :) keep up the great work

reviews.text: One of those brunch locations where waiting in line is worth it. The food always seems very well thought out, and the serving staff are very pleasant and quick. A note about the wait time, they always exaggerate the wait time. If you say it's a 30min wait, you won't ever have to wait that long (some exceptions may apply!). Their homemade breads are very tasty, and so far I haven't had anything disappointing to eat there. Their jerk chicken is exceptional.
great food, great service and very tolerable of children during breakfast. Our waitress was kind and polite and you could tell she loved children. The customer service added to an already tasty meal.
Very experienced servers and cooks.. Owner came and greeted us at the table.  Delicious specialties, all made from scratch.  Good for group brunch, but plan to wait or make a reservation.

As always....fantastic service  & I had the best omelette ever today for lunch! My monday didn't start very well with the car in the garage for a brake job but after lunch at Stone face,  I was smiling again. Thanks!!!

I've kept going back here a few times for lunch, dinner, new year's eve, business meetings, and more. They have never disappointed. I have found their food always very tasty, the service excellent. Their wine selection is pretty good. Their pricing is reasonable for the calibre of restaurant (food/service/location/etc) they are. There's a very low cost ($3/night) parking lot about 3 minute walk right across the street from them.

reviews.text:
Petit Bill's is one of my favourite places in Ottawa. It's a bit upscale: expect to pay about 20-30 per head without drinks. What I love about this place is that it isn't pretentious. The food is great, the service is friendly, and they care a lot. 

The owner will often swing by and ask how the food is. Another thing that's kind of cool about this place is that they make their own alcohol, when I was there they had spiced rum. It was fantastic.

Would recommend checking it out for a bit of French / Newfie cuisine!

My husband and I love coming to Petit Bill's. The service is always spot on (Terry and Cassie are great!) The food is amazing and the atmosphere is cozy. We really appreciate having a great restaurant in our neighbourhood. Kudos to the staff and owners for running such a hospitable restaurant that serves amazing food.

Excellent service and good food. Non pretentious, straightforward cooking here - great seafood options on the menu usually. Cozy and welcoming atmosphere. Go for the Jiggs dinner that they serve from time to time for a taste of Newfoundland.
Really friendly service. Food was fantastic. I felt like the owners would really get to know you if you went a few times. Comfy atmosphere
Great service and fantastic food.  Among the best selections of bourbon in the city

formatted_address: 1595 Merivale Rd, Nepean, ON K2G 3J4, Canada

reviews.text: Good selection of sea food.  Very friendly staff.  Nice, cozy atmosphere.
All you can eat shrimp. So good.

Fast and friendly service. Staff are polite and attentive. Food is delicious as always, and they're always adding something new to the menu. Waitress even gave me a take-away container of their infamous biscuits when I asked if that was possible.

I recently visited this establishment and I was not too impressed. First of all the waiter put a straw in my drink, I DID NOT ASK FOR A STRAW IN MY DRINK. Second of all they didn't have any tables smaller than for four people so I looked really awkward when I sat alone. Third of all the waiter forgot to tell my meal included seafood, which causes me digestive issues. This then caused me to exfoliate in my pants when the waiter startled me. When I complained the waiter got sassy with me and told me I should've know the lobster meal included seafood, and that If I couldn't hold it in my pants that was my problem. I then asked for the manager who turned out to be some white dude, who proceeded to tell me I couldn't speak English properly. I then lost my temper and tried to free all the lobsters from the aquariums, like what the heck this isn't sea world. This caused me to get ejected.

Just for the record sushi will always be better.

My name is Kenny and I'm a survivor

I almost never write any reviews but since  i am literally in pain right now i thought i need to vent here. 
Just left the restaurant 2 hours ago. I ordered the grilled dish of salmon, lobster, and shrimps 
besides the fact that the salmon and lobster tasted so bad, I got food poisoning and i am in lots of pain right now 
someone messed up in the kitchen !!

formatted_address: 585 Montreal Rd, Ottawa, ON K1K 4K4, Canada

Great service. I am not a beer drinker but there were other drinks to choose from, including a good cider. Nice atmosphere.
Amazing place. Very good beers, a lot of options to tasty. Is always crowded.

reviews.text: Love the ambiance, the service and the products.  Cigars and booze. Great lounge to kick back, smoke a cigar and drink. Large selection. Plenty of T.V.s to satisfy your sports addiction. Cheers

i don't smoke (well, except the cigarillo on very very special occasion) but one of my best friend does and when he's in town looking for a place to enjoy a smoke and drink, this is usually the place we stop at.

drinks are not bad, a bit pricey but normal for the neighborhood. the air filtration system does its job perfectly. you don't smell too much afterwards. waitresses are attentive enough making sure you're enjoying your time.

one thing i can say though, you're not allowed to smoke anything other than cigars which bummed my best friend as he's a big fan of the herb

Awful place. Well first I don't smoke so it's hard to judge. On a Friday night I just wanted to have a drink with my friends and all the bars were packed so we tried this one. Well, it is ridiculously expensive  (and I come from Monaco so seriously!) And the waitress was very rude, not taking care of us, nothing. When I left I said "thank you have a good evening" and she just picked that cash and went away. Not even a "thank you"??? You are never going to see me in this bar again!

My friends and I went for a night out recently at Stogies and were very well taken care of. The service and vibe were great. Moreover, this establishment also lets you bring your own cigars. That said, it also boats an impressive cigar selection in its on-site humidor.
Nice place to relax with friends, colleagues, clients.  I wish they had a nice resto downstairs.

Good place!

Le Omakase était très bon, à l'exception du dessert qui nous a vraiment déçu. Le service n'est par contre pas à la hauteur. Pas de gros problèmes, mais une foule de détails qui agacent : service des hommes avant les femmes, pas voir la bouteille quand on commande un vin au verre, la chaos qui a pris l'équipe quand le restaurant s'est rempli d'habitués. La facture reste salée pour 2 personnes.

Comme tout le monde, nous avions entendu parler en termes élogieux de ce restaurant désormais 'célèbre' à Montréal. Nous avions donc choisi d'y aller pour célébrer un anniversaire, le 6 juin dernier. Voici nos impressions:

- Décor ordinaire
- Service correct
- Menu dégustation: pour 65$ par personne, c'est une vraie blague (de mauvais goût)! Portions minuscules, préparations ordinaires, goût communs... Grosse déception!

Bref, il y a de biens meilleurs restaurants à bien meilleur prix à Montréal!

reviews.text: Went there for a friends birthday. Was not allowed to split a meal with a friend. So we decided to get some appetizers because we were both not very hungry. We were then told we had to spend minimum 20$ each. Three different waiters approached us while we were making our choices to hurry us up. So we ordered appetizers and desserts to share with everyone. Both appetizers and desserts were brought to us at the same time as everyone elses meals. Dissapointing service. Appetizers and desserts tasted pretty bland.
We go here for lunch often with my team.  The food is basic but the atmosphere is warm.  Good fries.  The meat is cooked in butter so you have to like this flavour.

Poor service. Your presence seem to annoy the waiter. Especially when you had to ask him to open your bottle of wine, mayo for fries, and anything really. Ordered the tuna. Not sure if I should have eaten it. It was cool inside and had juices like if it was freshly defrosted and all the food came out too fast. And poor quality tuna with grizzly stuff in it. Avoid disapointment and go to McDonald's at least you know what you would get and it won't be disappointment

Was looking forward to trying their fish and chips and a very very big disappointment when we were told that they have not served fish and chips for years. Our waiter didn't even bother to offer an alternative dish to us and spoke to us with a snobby attitude.  To Steak Frite: if you no longer serve a particular dish, then at least have the courtesy to take it off your website menu like that people wont be disappointed when they walk into your restaurant.
Food is fine but not worth the price. It's a bring your own wine. It feels industrial (service). Better places to see in Montreal, I would not recommend it.

Fast and Delicious ! The new Comme Chez Soi (it moved to a bigger place on St-Laurent) is much better. You have plenty of space to sit, the waiter was nice and well explained the menu, the food was fast served and tasted great. Price is a bit high at ~13$ for a Bison burger with aged cheddar and bacon, served with diced fried potatoes and a bit of salad. However the burger is big enough and i was happy with it. The lunch was worth the money. They also have a delicious huge lasagna ! Go try it now !
A perfect burger, but with no prices shown on the menu and outrageously expensive food you feel a bit cheated.
Love this restaurant, the location is super and the burger of fish that I had today was extraordinaire

Je vais au Comme Chez Soi pour l'heure du dîner car c'est près de mon travail. En plus du menu sur carte (crêpes, omelettes..), nous avons le choix de burgers et de lasagnes. 

Les 2 choix de Lasagne sont souvent au Bison et Végétarienne. Après 4 visites, la Lasagne Végétarienne n'était toujours disponible. Lorsque j'ai demandé pourquoi elle était toujours au tableau si elle n'était jamais disponible, la serveuse m'a ignoré et ne m'a pas répondu. 

Le décor est bien également et il y a assez de places pour le nombre de personnes qui y vont pendant l'heure du dîner. Si vous êtes 2 personnes et que le resto est presque vide, on vous refusera quand même de prendre une table pour 4 personnes. 

Outre le service que je trouve moyen, les gens qui travaillent sur place sont polis et souriants.

reviews.text: Meal was awesome, perfectly cooked. Our server was perfect, very distant and unobtrusive with us but also very involved with other tables... Really knew how to read the table and deliver appropriate service. We ended up seated right next to the wood fireplace in the first floor and it was lovely.

Nice ambience but very bad customer service. My friends and I were on a group tour in Canada. In an all expense paid tour we assumed that drinks like cranberry juice, orange juice and even wine were included in our 3 course meal. I mean this was our eighth day of tour and we never had to pay for drinks.

But as soon as we wanted to leave, the waiter said, "Wait you need to pay for your drinks." The issue here is NOT that we are not capable of paying for the drinks but it should be mentioned that drinks were not included before the waiter took the orders. They came and asked us as if the drinks were part of the paid meal. If they have mentioned this to us...we would just be happy drinking plain water.

Second time visiting, second time being served by Jimmy who was efficient and helpful. We had a lovely time indoors and out and the food was excellent too.
It's right next to the Keg, but honestly is way better with a much better atmosphere and quality of food

My husband and I came here during our honeymoon and we had the best meal of our stay in Montreal. He had the buffalo steak and raved about it and I had the cod. It literally melted in my mouth. He ordered the chocolate mousse cake and it was lovely. The apple tart was a little disappointing, especially the crust, but despite that, we really enjoyed our meal and wouldn't hesitate to recommend it.

The server was courteous and helpful when we sat down . However, one of the steak my party ordered was so full of  gristle that my friend cannot eat it. We informed the server and he took the steak away to the manager. He never be brought anything back to the table and when the rest of us (8 of us in the party). After we pay our tab, and ask about what had happened, the server said the manager offer my friend a piece of dessert. We declined the offer, but we feel very disappointed. My friend did not have his dinner and did not got any explanation, but he got to pay for a tough piece of meat.

Not my style, really. Too dark and serious for my personality. It's just a question of taste, so don't hesitate (food is good).

What a great experience from the minute I walked in the door to the last bite on my plate I couldn't have been more pleased what a great cozy atmosphere that Sherry  creates while sitting at the bar .great experience and will be back.. I eat all around the world and can be very fussy . they came through 100% as the chef also  was kind enough to come out and ask me how my meal was.

reviews.text:
First time going back to Bofinger in a long time and I came away really impressed. The restaurant itself is seriously nice on the inside and there is more than enough American-style BBQ meal items to choose from that there's just no way you won't find something that fits the bill. 

Prices are fair, but if you're looking for a great deal, look no further than the lunch express menu which is a great value. The pulled pork sandwich in particular is delicious. Great place to go to as a huge gang and watch hockey too.
Stopped in while on a business trip to Montreal and was completely blown away. Delicious Pinot BBQ sandwich and great fries. I will definitely eat here again on my next trip!

It's an awesome place, the staff is friendly, the owner is very nice. The food there is delicious and made with care, they have a patio that you can enjoy a nice cold beer under the sun. This place is very dog-friendly. I brought my dog on the patio and the waiter offered to bring water for my dog. I love Bofinger NDG.
Good food good prices, fun atmosphere!

Ordered a Beef Rib and Quarter Chicken Plater with Mac and Cheese.
For such an expensive place, you have to order at a counter and you only get served after seating yourself. Also was charged an extra 5$, they claimed that my beef rib was "bigger than usual" so THEY decided to charge me extra, even though I did not order it to be a larger portion. Also the price on the menu did not match the price on my receipt.
Food was not so great, only 'okay' item was the roast chicken leg in my order. Mac and cheese had very runny sauce, no cheese taste at all, like KD with too much milk.
Not a recommended place to eat.

reviews.text: Ok, first impression for Sunday Brunch is should I stay or should I go... Seems like very crowded and compact. But turned out food and is superb service is excellent. Waitress friendly and smiling. Warm ambiance. Won't doubt again....

A perfect French style Brunch.
 French Style Brunch Definition: A kind of brunch that you eat to enjoy and not to stuff yourself for the next three days. 
If you make it there at ten a.m during the weekends, you would not have to line up for a long time. I tried the omelet and the very smell of it just blew me away. Bravo Lawrence.

Fine cuisine, did not expect that quality of food. I was looking for a regular brunch but I have to admit it's the best brunch I had in Montreal so far :) I had scramble eggs and salmon, amazing taste! and the organic apple juice... ♡
Tasty brunch!  The late I got was on the bitter side but the late art was nice. The decor was nice and the couch surprisingly comfortable.  Friendly staff too.

Nice place for brunch with cozy and friendly ambience. I had kedgeree and liked it a lot. It's very delicious but because it was mainly fried rice, next time I would order it for lunch instead of brunch.

reviews.text: Excellent, innovative cuisine and exemplary service made for a memorable evening. Gilbert at the bar, Normand, Pierre, Luka, and their talented team in the kitchen are a winning combination!!!

Fascinating menu.
Impeccable attention to detail.
Engaged service.

Nous avons pris le menu dégustation... J'étais certaine qu'on se foutait de ma gueule tellement les portions étaient minuscules mais surtout sans goût! Les 2 premières ne goûtaient que le vinaigre et les autres tellement fades! Pour donner un show et t'éduquer sur la provenance des aliments, pour ça ils sont les champions! Mais nous payé presque 600$, c'était pour un repas hors paire, pas pour me faire dire que le vin que j'allais boire allait goûter et sentir le vieux tuyau d'arrosage... PIRE DÉCEPTION le Toqué.

Évidemment, l'accueil et le service sont parfaits et les plats exquis. Cependant, pour le prix (très élevé), je n'y ai pas trouvé la magie et l'authenticité qu'on peut retrouver chez d'autres adresses prestigieuse à Montréal.

Le restaurant  profite de sa réputation pour afficher des prix exorbitants mais ne tient pas ses promesses. Très déçue pour les entrées et les plats qui sont bons mais n'ont rien d'extraordinaire. En revanche, bravo au chef pâtissier qui a fait un vrai travail sur les textures et les saveurs. Tous les desserts de la carte étaient délicieux ! 
Rien à redire non plus sur le service. À la fin du repas, nous avons eu droit à une visite guidée de la cuisine et de la cave à vin.

reviews.text:
An experience worth having. Service was reasonable, very well-timed and polite. Although I believe our server to be more articulate in French than English. Ambiance was fantastic and the environment - classic. French cuisine is not typically my favourite, but this restaurant has made me enjoy it a bit more! 

Lobster entree and shrimp appetizer were fantastic. The rabbit appetizer was not for my palette, but the venison entree was delightful. Wine pairing was immaculate, and I believe largely the reason for the five star reviews. Dessert was delicious and beautifully plated.

Overall, a great choice of restaurant in a city where great culinary choices are abundant.

I ate here on a Sunday night alone at the bar. I had the tasting menu. It was very good. The early dishes, razor clams and others, were good. As the meal progressed, however, it was outstanding.  I did the wine pairing, which was clever. I am on oenophile,  and I was impressed. A few of the choices were not the best in my view (a mets adult would have been better with the poached lobster and sweetbreads) in my view, but it was damn clever.  The staff were exceptionally professional. And I will absolutely go back. This is a first class establishment.

Exceptional food experience. Well worth the cost. We appreciate the fact that our 9 year old was not treated like a baby - as some waiters tend to do. He loved the food as much as we did. Highly recommend.

Incredible experience for my wife and I. We chose to do the tasting menu with the wine pairing. Each dish floored us in its taste and presentation. We wanted a special night for our getaway in Montreal and Bouillon Bilk gave is that and more. Exceptional!

Bouillon Bilk is an exceptional restaurant.  My past experiences there have suggested this, but I had it driven home again this week by the contrast with a meal there and at another slightly more expensive restaurant.  Bouillon Bilk had a better atmosphere and better service – with a waiter who ensured you completely understood the dish, rather than just the primary ingredient.  The food at Bouillon Bilk was in another class entirely.  The portions are not large, but quite filling and make it possible to have an appetizer and desert without feeling you’ll explode.  And the balance of the meal is exceptional.  The ingredients complement each other.  There is no side dish that’s randomly glued onto the main, but a complete dish where the flavours and textures combine and play off each other.  Not cheap, but worth every cent.

This is a very nice place. Music, ambiance, decor, wide variety of choices for tasty food. Service on lunch hour on a weekday was rapid. I have one experience so far but not my last here.

I used to love this place, but today there was a cockroach in my food!!!  They were very sorry but I still can't think of any reason for what happened other than the place is infested with cockroaches, it's winter very cold outside no way it came from the exterior.  Very disappointed and very sorry,  worst experience ever.
Good quality food overall. Service has improved comparing to a few years back.
AVOID, avoid, avoid... bad service. dirty washrooms,,,,

reviews.text: Great Italian food. Portions are large and price is very reasonable. The place is very loud. So if your looking for a great place to eat and have a good time with friends this would be it. If your looking for a romantic dinner for 2, I would avoid. Never any issues and I go on the regular.

Almost avoided this place because of the reviews. Made a reservation and got seated at a table we didn't like. We complained and got a new table, no problem.

Service was friendly. Food was quick. Sat near the front, had a good view of the staff and how they work. The manager was very detail oriented and greeted us in the beginning and asked us how we enjoyed our meal in the end. I was impressed and very happy for this.

We both had the pizza. It was very good. The bread however is under average. But it's free. This place is BYOB, so that's a plus.

The atmosphere in the main room is very good. A bit too loud and the place was about half full. I would suggest keeping the televisions on mute, as even a low volume only adds to the problem. 

We came to scout the place for a friend who is organizing a party. Not ready to recommend just yet. We'll be back to try the pasta.

One of the best Italian restaurants in the city and it's a bring your own wine as well! Expect long waits for the food but once it comes, it makes it all worth it. Huge place with a beautiful terrrasse! A must when in Montreal!  Fridays and Saturdays are really really busy - the weekdays are still busy but more relaxed and faster to get your food! Live music on weekends - love it!

Room was cold, some people had to have their coat on, bread was cold with plain cheap oil, chipped plates and glasses, no wine glass (yeah... you are stuck drinking wine in dolarama like glasses...), almost non existent service, cook screwed up portions and people went hungry. These people have no clue how to deal with groups...
Very impressed, one of the best pizzas I have had in long time. And the service was top notch, extremely friendly. Loved it

reviews.text: Took my mother (and family) out for her birthday on Saturday.  We had 5 Star service from our waiter JP (thank you) and the food was outstanding!!! Started with avocado rolls, calamari, cheese soup.... Ribs on the kids menu!!!  It was an overall WOW!!!!  We will be back!!!

Great selection of salads. I had the Indo-China salad which was amazing. The portion is huge and I ate the whole thing because it was so good. They didn't have many of the cheesecakes so that was a bit disappointing. The carrot cake was delicious but the frosting was regular cream and not cream cheese frosting...

Great restaurant! I really love the Saturday cheddar beer soup and their avocado rolls. I bring friends over there quite frequently. 4 stars because sometimes service is amazing and then sometime I get the day that I feel all alone in there.
The restaurant has a great ambiance and atmosphere.  The food was enjoyable and reasonably priced for what you got.  They have a wide selection of dessert and the staff was friendly and helpful.
It's overpriced, over stuffed menu, without a purpose. This restaurant, I believe, solely exists so people can feel rich while becoming poor and experiencing a poor meal.

The tartare is incredible and the ambience is great
A great steakhouse !!! Food is excellent as well as the service. All this sums up for a  relatively pricey tab however.

Portions are great, excellent variety in the menue. Service is good. Loved it. I will probably come back and with the offer at costco you pay 80$ and you get a 2 gift certificates of 50$. Nice wine selection starting at 10$ more than saq price and it goes over to 200$.
Portions sont bonnes, la variété du menu est excellente . Le service est bon. Nous allons probablement revenir.

Food and service are really nice. Space between tables and on tables are good, you don't feel crowded. Pricey but the food quality is on par with the price.

I recommend it.

Great place to get ramen and a few other Japanese/fusion delicacies. Especially on the weekends, however, it does get quite loud and obnoxious. Choose your night well!
Great idea but it's super loud and no matter where you sit you leave stinking of "grill"
CRAZY FUN!!

Avec montréal a rabais. Et le gérant le 26 mai. Très très très déçu. J'arrive à 5hrs chez imadake. Le staff de Montréal à rabais n'est pas arriver, (j'ai acheter un coupon qui donne droit à une consommation, un saké et de la bouffe) pour ma commande le gérant me dit qu'il me donne une consommation en attendant le staff de Montréal à rabais. Je prends ma consommation et la le staff de mtl à rabais arrive. Je leur donne mon coupon de bière, en voulant enfin celle à quelle j'avais droit et la il me refuse ma consommation me disant que c'était pour me faire patienter que j'avais eu la première consommation. Bon ok sa va. Je veut maintenant consommer de la bouffe et il me dise que je ne peut pas à cause que pour manger il ne sont pas pret ,je leur dit que je vais payer ma deuxième bière et que je veut manger, mais la le staff  de chez imadake n'est pas prêt à servir la bouffe et je ne peut avoir de bière car pour manger il fait prendre de l'alcool bref, payer mon coupon une bière un saké pas de bouffe toute mes félicitation au gérant. Wow qu'elle belle façon de traiter vos client. Je voulais vous racheter une consommation jusqu'à ce que vous osez prêt à servir de la bouffe et vous avec refuser. Très très très déçu.... voila mon expérience chez imadake.

reviews.text: This my favorite Italian restaurant in Montreal when I'm craving for a Tortellini Rossini. As for their pizza, they are good but nothing spectacular. For those who love thin crust pizza this could be a great place for you.

This is an amazing local restaurant. The place is bring your own wine, which is great. The pizza and pasta selection are incredible. The best thing on their menu however is the meat ball appetizers! Absolutely amazing atmosphere and decor. Service is good for a pretty busy restaurant. Be prepared for a line if you go during peak hours. This restaurant is always packed!

Bring your own wine!  A low cost restaurant.  Nice sidewalk seating. The food is good but matches the price point.  My salad with parm cheese had a very limited amount of cheese. But hey!  It was tasty.  A lovely summer spot close to the Jean Talon market.  A good bet if you are watching your wallet.

I hold pizza to a very high standard and this place didn't disappoint.  Excellent prosciutto pie.  Option to buy beer and wine across the street.  Friendly staff and reasonable prices. 5 minute walk from the market.  You won't be disappointed.

This isn't pizza. Pizza has flavour, this was just a piece of bread with plain toppings. What's with the menu? Why do you need that many pizza and pasta variety ? If the quality of food was amazing, they would only need a smaller menu. Service was quick but it's too be expected when food taste terrible. Zero love was put into it . A frozen pizza has more attention than this crap.

formatted_address: 1230 Boulevard de Maisonneuve O, Montréal, QC H3G 1M2, Canada
name: La Brasserie le Pois Penche

The food here is quite good. We were here on Thursday evening and the place was packed and loud. I found the atmosphere interesting, but my wife prefers calmer, quieter restaurants. reviews.text: When I need furniture or home accessories, IKEA is my go-to spot. If you're looking for something specific, you can easily check if it's available on their website to save yourself a trip (the downside: inventory is sometimes inaccurate for quick-selling, assorted products like plants, and you can't reserve certain products by phone). If you don't know exactly what you want, you could easily spend a whole day browsing as they have a food court (with decent prices) to keep you fueled. But the best part about IKEA is its affordability. You can get furniture that actually looks nice for half the price of other furniture stores. It might not always be solid wood, and assembling it can be a hassle, but it can last a long time. In fact, our IKEA bookcases, chests of drawers, desks, and bed frame have lasted us over fifteen years so far. (Their couches aren't the best on the market, though.) The wait at the cash is usually very short, even during closing time when hundreds of people start flocking towards the exit, but I can't say the same for the returns and exchanges section, especially on weekends. I once waited an hour to return something. (On the bright side, if you're quick enough, you can do all your shopping and be back in time for your turn.) Missing parts are not uncommon, but IKEA is quick to replace them for you without a problem. A tip: if you're buying furniture, always plan appropriate transportation, because IKEA's shipping fees are steep (especially compared to many furniture stores who ship for free). Their parking lot is massive, but always seems to get filled up. It's quite a testament to the store's popularity! Now if only they were located in a more easily accessible area of the city...

We had a delicious meal here and excellent service. I especially loved the salami and cheese platters we had and the warm bread knots were delicious. We got a great wine recommendation that matched our meal perfectly and was delicious. The service was also excellent, everyone was so nice and helpful and professional!
Love the food, service & atmosphere.  I don't go back to restaurants often when they are this pricey & there are so many options in the city but I find myself drawn back here time & time again.

Best pasta I ever had! Although I haven't tried that many. I usually go for pizza at an Italian restaurant but decided to try something different. Got the spaghetti alla carbonara ($19) and it was delicious. Pasta was fresh, top quality ingredients and flavourful. Would appreciate if it was more in quantity and if they served bread before the meal.

Had a work conference at the Holiday inn. Breakfast was included, the hot breakfast was good and simple. Lunch was sandwhiches and salad with a great selection of desserts. The room was good, chairs are uncomfortable after hours of sitting. Meeting accommodations like audio and visual worked perfectly.
Very nice place for hosting conferences and business meetings. Good food and good rooms and good location..tight off the QEW. Very easy to find
Clean and customer service was excellent

I loved it because the staff was very friendly and breakfast was delicious. Also, the rooms were cleaned daily and provided an excellent view. Room did not have a terrible smell unlike other hotels around the area.

An awesome place to go out and have fun. Cold beverages, great music selection and happy people dancing all the time.

Its a good place for cheap drinks but don't bother ordering food. 

The waitresses are nice but only a few of them are genuinely willing to serve you. I've been here a couple times and there are some waitresses that are very short and rude. Watch out for them! Switch waitresses early on if you sense trouble because it doesn't get any better.  

The security guards will turn you away if you aren't wearing proper attire even though the place is ratchet. The dress code doesn't make sense because its not the most classy place to drink. 

You get what you pay for.

Girls!! Be careful with Security Guards in this Place!! My friends and I had a really bad experience last night with 3 of their security men of this  place!! They don´t now what respect for women is!! We will never go to this place again! Ever!

One of the security staff ask us to leave our table, supposedly was reserved for someone else's the host didn't say that when she gave it to us and and the worst is that they start pushing a girl to leave the table. Tried to talk to them to stop and instead they all went to us and said we were threatening them. Lost a scarf and food we ordered. We called the police and we are continuing in the process of the physical treatment she went through. Watch out girls, worst place to stop by.

Great Place! X'mas eve,  night show,  had a great time,  you should come & explore!
Mixed latino oriented bar and club on College West. High energy and fun.
I like the diversity of people going to this place. They have latin music on Saturdays, but I think they changed the Dj and he really needs to know what actually latin music is.

Will be back.

I got a deal that included valet parking

Hotel is in a great location, parking is convenient, front desk and valet staff are good, rooms are typical.  We had no issue except that prepaid breakfast  with the Fuel up for Free offer is disappointing.  How can you mess up breakfast??  1.  Serve crappy coffee (Starbucks is around the corner) 2. Provide poor service.  ie make sure all serving staff disappear at the same time. Repeatedly run out of juice glasses, etc.  Food was consistently mediocre.  We stayed 4 nights, 1st breakfast was Ok , 2nd became a little painful, 3rd was  the breaking point. 4th was enjoyed elsewhere.Would stay again but no more breakfast.
This was a very comfortable place to stay, and it has a great location in Toronto. I recommend it!
Nice hotel...close to bars and short walk to convention center

name: Red Lobster

reviews.text: Well... it is popular for a reason! Great prices on seafood-- but stick to the basics. Steamed lobster, crabs legs, with simple butter-- dishes (pasta, shrimps in sauce) were very salty and couldn't pinpoint the ingredients (ie: dumped out of a bag from the freezer?). Basic seafood was excellent value. Free salad and the most tasty biscuits this side of the border (who gives free bread at the table anymore?). This place feels nostalgic, but as someone used to downtown restaurant prices, I was extremely impressed with the value for $32.50-- lobster, shrimp and crab (check out the photo!) Service was good and staff were friendly. Would definitely go again if I had a craving for steamed seafood--can't beat the price and the free biscuits were.... heaven.

I go here regularly but infrequently. Sometimes the experience is inconsistent. Out of menu items or poorly plated but other times it is a great meal with great service. My last meal there was one of those. The experience I hope for.  I have a lot of fond memories of the chain from my childhood I and love when it is great.
Me and my family have been going to this location for more than 15 years. Food is always good. Staff are always friendly and service is fast and reliable.

We had a bit of a wait for a table but the food was worth it. Had the endless shrimp which is way more than you can really it but tasty. My husband had a seafood bake which he raved about and which looked really good buy I couldn't try because of the scallops.
The Kids menu options I think could do with a refresh but all in all I thought it was a good experience
Only been once for lunch and it was good.  We had a big table and service was pretty quick.  Staff was great and accommodating.

adr_address: 220 Yonge St, Toronto, ON M5B 2H1, Canada
formatted_address: 220 Yonge St, Toronto, ON M5B 2H1, Canada
name: CF Toronto Eaton Centre

reviews.text:
Went the the day after boxing day and they were very busy. The supposed deals were just items marked up to mark down. We were hungry and wanted a quick bite to eat and it took us 20 Min to fight for a table and another 10 Min to get 4 chairs. The mall was well decorated and I did feel the holiday spirit with some amazing decorations. 

The best part of my visit to the Eaton Centre was that my wife didn't buy anything since they were so busy. Would not go again but was good exercise walking from one side to the other.

Venerable, cavernous Shopping Centre smack in the middle of downtown Toronto. Used to be anchored by a huge and impossibly busy Sears store up to about 2014/15 (even Canadians have rejected Sears). Not as option-filled as the massive Square One in Mississauga, say, but presents reasonable shopping options to those looking to do a quick one-stop shopping and entertainment trip when in the City Centre. The hot dogs outside are pretty decent too.

Good:
Very well decorated with lots of people taking pictures of the displays (Christmas time).  Too many stores to visit in one day.  Good sales saving my bank account. Additional staff scattered throughout at stationary locations to help direct you through the massive mall. Clean.  Security meandering here and there. Good food located on the bottom floor and little places throughout.  

Bad: 
Higher class, so the prices usually follow.  If you're looking to be really thrifty, your options will be limited.  

Ugly:
A couple stores had their alarms going off regularly. It got a little annoying while in those stores, and then sort of stressed me out when I went to leave because it could be a little embarrassing. 

Over all:
Great experience and I'm looking forward to going back soon.

They have found way to good way to segregate by disposable income. I guess that's good. most "Flagship" stores are fairly small. Good location if you live downtown, parking and access is ridiculously expensive.

Great place for tourist, to take pictures. Especially around this time where they have the huge trees and glowing reindeer. There's also a good selection of mid-high end stores. The mall itself is connected to the PATH system in Toronto so its a lot easier for people to avoid the cold, while wanting to travel around the city.

reviews.text: I have never felt more ripped off ordering a salad before, ever. My mom and I ordered an $18 pizza (which was okay) and a $15 salad to share. The salad was an absolute joke. There was hardly any lettuce on the small plate, a few beets and I actually had to examine it VERY closely to find the goat cheese or nuts. We ate it in about 4 bites... A $15 salad... I cannot believe it. I ordered a side salad with my meal at Canyon Creek last night and it had about 4x more lettuce than this sad-looking, overpriced salad.

A nice cozy restaurant with some great food.  I had the Buffalina pizza and a glass of the dark lager. The pizza was good but I thought it was terrible that they don't cut the pizza into slices for you.  I was provided with a steak knife to cut the pizza myself and that was a disaster - all the cheese came off the pizza, the slices were uneven, everything turned out messy -  it's such a shame that they expect their guests to cut their own pizza, shame on you for ruining the experience!  The service was efficient, perhaps not the most welcoming (she seemed annoyed - maybe because we were a party of 15).   I love how they have customizable $15 gin and tonics where you are able to choose the type of gin, tonic and garnish you want.  The prices are a bit expensive here, salads starting at around $20 and pints starting at $9.  Don't get me wrong, the food is really good but the bill racks up fast here when you're wining and dining.  The restaurant itself is very cozy, a good atmosphere with an excellent selection of oldies being played.  Although my first experience here was mediocre, I can't say I would never come back here,  maybe one day.

It's unassuming from the outside but the service and quality of food is fantastic! You wouldn't know it was part of the large Terroni group of restaurants. The pasta is made in house, the ingredients are authentic! The staff are attentive and know the menu. The ambiance is great from sitting at the bar, shared long table or individual personal tables. The desserts are also made in house!
Food, wine, atmosphere, excellent coffee, and service from friendly staff. Couldn't be happier, deffinate pick me up, made my day!
The food was outstanding, the service was amazing, and the restaurant was beautiful! Will definitely be going back!

Can't go wrong with $4 pints

reviews.text: Good food and service for Sunday brunch. Half price champagne and sparkling wine for Sunday brunch.
The lasagna is really good and our server was fantastic!

Went there for dinner with a friend, and we had a nice night. We went in without any expectations of what we "felt" the restaurant had to be or what we "deserved", and were rewarded with great food, nice wine, i cannot however say that we were fans of the dessert. People please remember that restaurants have standards, so if they regularly cut their pizza in 4, don't expect that because there are 7 of you that that will change.  Also read the menu on the site before going to decide if the price is right for you, don't go in and complain after the fact.

Had a reservation for 7 people. When we arrived they kept us waiting for about 15 minutes. Nice table, nice atmosphere, but overpriced. The service and food is very poor. Had to ask several times for cutlery and condiments. My wife had a shrimp pasta dish which had a handful of pasta and two shrimp! The small portions of food were overall bland and not worth the price. Had a pizza ordered for the 7 of us and it arrived cut in 4. Wait times where long and they forgot things. They had the gall to charge an 18% gratuity on top of it all. Would not go back. To many good places in the city to bother going back here.
The pizza is just okay here. Much better at Libretto. Though the ambiance is great and classy.

formatted_address: 236 Adelaide St W, Toronto, ON M5H 1W7, Canada
name: Yuzu No Hana

reviews.text:
This isn't your regular sushi place. The quality of the fish served here is much higher than your regular neighborhood sushi joint. Not only do you get a wide variety, the fish itself is just simply...  Better.  Perhaps their source is different than  the run of the mill sushi suppliers that 90%+ of restaurants use here. 

A unique reason why you'd want to go here is you can sample fish that is not usually available in this part of the world. They offer a selection of off the menu items sourced from Tsujiki fish market flown in from Tokyo. Be adventurous and try something unexpected and new...  Like flounder and Japanese horse mackerel. 

Sushi is taken seriously here... The rice used is simply masterful. You can taste the flavour and texture of each individual grain in every bite. 

The kitchen items are equally masterful. Try the soft shelled crab. It's coated in fermented puffed rice before frying.... Again, another example of the chefs  elevating food to a new, rare, and sometimes unexpected level. 

Yuzu no hana is worth a visit. Sure, your paying more than a night at your neighborhood sushi joint, but it's worth it to have a uniquely masterful experience.

The food in general was good. We were very disappointed with the Yusu dinner which included seven courses for $70.00 per person. When we looked over to the people next to us who were having the bento box, that costs only $30.00, we noticed that the items were very similar.  For more than double the price, we expected something better. To top it off, the seventh item was the ice cream which is  only $4.00 on the regular menu.  Again, expected something elevated. So disappointing! Food was good but don't waste your money on that menu item.

1. No tea served (usually should be free/complimentary) upon seating
    Water was given however not refilled after 1 glass
2. Menu is a jumbled mess. Too much information overload. Way too    complicated, it's sushi! 
Very hard to understand if you're a novice sushi goer
3. Lighting is poor - you will need a flashlight or use your phone to see the menu
4. Staff/Servers - not helpful (I've gone twice, same experience) Something as simple as 'what do you recommend as a main that has crab' seems like rocket science. 
I was given a recommendation. Then was brought out 4 pathetic pieces that were insanely overpriced ($30+)

Food was decent however for the price and service it's terrible value for the money you'll spend.
I don't recommend nor will I go back; even if it's free

Mediocre especially for downtown.
The spicy tuna was way too spicy not like other restaurants.
They served us wooden disposable chopsticks.
The dragon and eel roll was a joke. It was way too warm in temperature.
The tempura was too greasy. The cooks are all new.  
The sashimi was the only good dish.

Same owner as Japango which is my favourite sushi place in the city. Husband runs Yuzu and wife runs Japango. Sushi is top quality but be prepared to pay for it. Find Yuzu to be more upscale and geared towards business accounts.

Fantastic authentic Irish pub. A hidden gem!
I'm a repeat customer. I love the atmosphere, the service is always good and the food is even better.
Serves a lot of Guinness so it's definitely fresh and tastes good
Awesome place to be with friends.. Old fashioned Irish pub with great variety of beers on tap plus food..

Most of the eagerness Filipinos and their costumer service skills are so great. Will cone back here
It's nice to have coffee with friends. I prefer the coffee at Tim's Scarborough Town Centre. Clean people are nice.

This is a small location so there isn't much room can move around. It's located in a commercial area so there's a lot of blue shirt workers coming in for their cup of joe. The staff are friendly and efficient.
Fast service on the drive thru.
Great for wifi and the usual Tim Hortons fare, drive thru is almost always busy during the day, parking can get tight

adr_address: 218 Adelaide St W, Toronto, ON M5H 1W7, Canada
formatted_address: 218 Adelaide St W, Toronto, ON M5H 1W7, Canada

reviews.text: Great food with wide selection. Great for groups to eat at while visiting Toronto. This place is the only place that will give you top notch poutine. I had a wonderful experience there as well as the rest of my family did. The meal goes great before you visit the CN Tower!

This was my first time eating poutine, and it was so good that I had it twice during my time in Toronto. While this is clearly not the healthiest option, the food is so good. There are so many different varieties and the service is fast and friendly!

LOVE the music they play, love the poutine, one of the best I've ever had. I'm not giving 5 stars because I feel like the quality went a bit down compared to a couple of years ago, also they have probably the worst logo I've ever seen!

Place was very dirty. Flies everywhere even in the ketchup... and it's winter... I had the Philly cheese steak poutine and it was subpar at best. It made me sick about am hour later. To top it off they had a good deal with buying a $25 gidt card you get a free poutine. She failed to mention that until after my $18 purchase.
Good service, big portions (even the snack size is filling), and generally good food. You can choose your toppings or order something off their menu.

formatted_address: 1475 The Queensway, Etobicoke, ON M8Z 1T3, Canada

reviews.text: I am not the type to write bad reviews but after what I experienced  (today) it sadness me to say that it was by far the most unprofessional, disrespectful and rude  customer service experience I have ever had. The store manager was rude, and refused to listen or even help. She also implied that my father and I were lying about the situation. I purchased a "high quality" IKEA mattress 4 years ago which broke down in less than 2 years of use. I sleep on it during the summer only as I am away for school. I used it over the Christmas break and it really caused me serious back pain because it just sunk in. I do admit that I lost the receipt but had a bank statement....as a company that "stands by" and "honors" their products you should have a better method of handling this. I was also lied to by the manager and the person helping me on the phone, I am not perfect but how dare they question my honesty and values? I will definitely be returning the other mattresses bought late last year as I am worried that they will get destroyed within a couple of years. Please feel free to contact me if you want anymore details, I will gladly provide ikea with the name of the manager as she really does require retraining. I am not looking for a free product nor my money back, and in all honesty, you guys just lost 5 loyal customers for the past 11 years. Best wishes.

Very good IKEA, has everything you would need. I would advise to come during off peak hours as ques can become very long at certain times. This place is a great place to test your patience with your partner, with so many great options you'll learn how to compromise. I would wholly recommend this store, make sure to get a hotdog and frozen yogurt.
Great experience very friendly staff. I dropped my key in IKEA and they actually helped me in finding it. Highly recommend to shop here!
I love exploring Ikea , you never know what treasures you will find . Plus they it very affordable . Lets not forget the yummy meatballs . Happy shopping
Its okay and I love their restaurant. Well stocked inventory. Havent seen any monkey though.

reviews.text: The food was okay, prices are competitive with other ramen restaurants. I like how they have the $1 upgrade option to large, but the extra noodles you get with this upgrade is barely noticeable. It would also be nice if they were able to add more soup instead of just more noodles. Overall, taste is okay for the price you pay but there are definitely better ramen restaurants in Toronto.

I like the place and the food is nice, but the place is a little too dark. It's not too dark not see what you're doing, but still dark enough to think that the place is only lit up by one lamp. They're trying to go for something that looks like natural lighting, but it's too dark.

I liked the noodles and the takoyaki they served.

Service was very fast and portions were good. Some of the best takoyaki I've had in Toronto. Ramen could be improved a bit with thicker noodles, but that may just be my preference. If Sansotei is too lined up, this is a very reasonable alternative just down the street.
nice comfy place. service is quick and snappy. the decor and seating are much much better than other ramen places I have been to. the food is great as well.
Good prices and great food! They have vegan and vegetarian options. Staff are incredibly friendly
